## 1. WHAT WAS BUILT

Demo name: Compliance Reconciliation Console
Demo URL (local): /demos/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi/
Demo URL (live): https://michaelwegter.com/demos/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi/
Work-sample route: https://michaelwegter.com/work-samples/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi

Concept: A self-contained fiscal XML compliance console. The user picks one of two SAF-T
fixture files, watches a live streaming-parse memory chart animate (iterparse vs naive DOM
load, projected to 250,000 elements / 500MB-equivalent), sees the format detector output
schema version, country, accounting basis, and routed parser profile from the first 2KB,
then steps through 10 named reconciliation rules with adjustable thresholds and click-through
drill-down to the exact offending records. A second tab paginates a 100,000-row generated
ledger with sort and CSV export.

