## 3. FEATURES DELIVERED

HERO — Streaming parse + reconciliation rules engine with drill-down
  - Format detector reads first 2KB, identifies xmlns namespace against a 3-entry schema
    registry (SAF-T PT 1.04, SAF-T PT 1.03, SAF-T NO), outputs country, variant, version,
    accounting basis, and routed parser profile
  - Animated memory chart: two SVG polylines grow in real time over a 2.2s animation.
    The streaming line holds near constant (~12 MB peak). The naive line climbs linearly to
    ~10,012 MB at 250,000 projected elements. Honest disclaimer below the chart explains
    the production vs demo distinction.
  - 10 rules evaluate against the parsed fixture. Each card shows id, name, what it checks,
    pass/warn/fail badge, record count, adjustable threshold slider, and (for failures) a
    click-to-expand drill table showing Locator, Found, Expected, Delta.
  - Anomalies fixture triggers 4 real failures immediately on load, giving the client
    something concrete to click before reading a word of the cover letter.

SUPPORTING 1 — Analytical dashboard
  - 5 summary tiles (documents parsed, source rows, rules passed, warnings, failures)
  - 12-bar anomaly trend chart (flagged rows by fiscal period from the 100k dataset)
  - Ledger table: 100,000-row dataset generated on first dashboard visit (deferred to avoid
    blocking first paint), paginated 50 rows/page (2,000 pages), sortable on 8 columns,
    CSV export button for current page view

SUPPORTING 2 — File-format detector
  - Embedded in the file bar section above the streaming panel
  - Detects document type, schema variant, country, schema version, fiscal period, accounting
    basis, and routed parser profile from the first 2,048 bytes
  - Different result shown for clean (1.04_01, F basis, Portugal) vs anomalies (1.03_01, C basis)

