## 4. SELF-TEST RESULTS

Build: npm run build -> success, 650ms, zero errors, zero warnings
      dist/ output confirmed to include demos/full-stack-developer-python-fastapi/ with all assets.

JS syntax: node --check passed on all 4 JS files (app.js, parser.js, rules.js, data.js).

Rule logic trace (anomalies fixture):
  R03 invoice VAT sum = 2391.50, ledger VAT sum (acct 24320000) = 2403.50, delta = 12.00 EUR
      -> FAIL (default threshold 10 EUR, delta exceeds it). Drill shows reconciliation row.
  R04 invoice sequence: FT 2023/1 -> FT 2023/2 -> FT 2023/3 -> FT 2023/4 -> FT 2023/6 (gap=1)
      -> FAIL (default max-gap = 1, gap found = 1, exclusive threshold). Drill shows gap row.
  R07 FT 2023/4: GrossTotal 1267.40 vs NetTotal 1030.00 + TaxPayable 236.90 = 1266.90, delta 0.50
      -> FAIL (default tolerance 0.01 EUR). Drill shows offending invoice row.
  R09 FT 2023/9 CustomerID C999 not in MasterFiles (6 registered: C001-C006)
      -> FAIL. Drill shows orphan row.
  All other rules (R01, R02, R05, R06, R08, R10) -> PASS on anomalies fixture.

Clean fixture: All 10 rules PASS. Format detector outputs SAF-T PT 1.04_01, F (invoicing only).

---

## 5. PROTOTYPE VS FULL DECISION

Outcome: LEAN FULL (no fallback rule tripped).
No backend required. No Vite sub-build required. Self-contained static app.

The one honest stub (per plan.md): the memory chart visualizes the bounded-memory iterparse
algorithm projected to 250,000 elements / 500MB-equivalent. The browser parses the shipped
fixture with DOMParser. Production uses lxml.iterparse server-side. The chart and the
stream-disclaimer text both state this. This matches plan.md section 2 exactly.

